cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with generating Chinese characters with specified styles, which involves image processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel model that integrates different modules, which could fall under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with generating and manipulating graphical representations of Chinese characters, which could also fall under the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
